When to use:
  You don't want to deal with the accursed curses.
  You want to use multiple windows (e.g, MDI)
  You just want color/attributes, without dealing with the accursed curses
  You need to do do curses on files other than stdout.

When not to use:
  When you've got to support non-typical terminals


The Modules:
  escape.py
    Various escape sequences.
  lineread.py
    To get a line of input. Has a shoddy history buffer that can be disabled.
  termwindow.py
    Creates output-only terminal windows.
  termbuffer.py
    Only print out changes to the terminal window
